  "duration": 125.544372864,
  "text": " Hi, this is Ibiar from Bimsword International and in this video you will learn how to manage your corporate memory more efficiently thanks to Eva. Let's get started. On a previous video, I introduced the document management module where we can create libraries, documents and folders. The menu on top allows us to create a new library and to access the operations and report sections to for example add a virtual folder or to load the library history. Whenever you select one of libraries you will be able to access the organize open and share sections too some of the properties you can access are the general ones where you can see the path the creation date the owner you can also modify the new file properties to associate for example a profile to every new file or the document properties where you can decide if you want to keep every version of the document create a workflow or digitally sign a document the access to the document management system is restricted based on authorizations which can be managed clicking on the security icon The authorizations are organized based on who is the owner and which users roles positions professions departments and groups have access to the file system We can define general authorizations for the libraries and then start restricting the permissions for certain folders and documents. Here you can see the permissions are classified into three groups, View, Modify and Annotation. Each of them has subgroups of permissions, making it really easy to allow or deny access to users to view, download, edit or delete files. I will access the HR library and then the Clearance folder to open one of the documents. IBA can open files in many different formats, such as PDF, DOC or Excel, and it can even play videos. IBA has an integrated viewer so we can access the documents without having to download them. Thank you so much for watching. If you liked this video, don't forget to give it a thumbs up and subscribe to our channel. If you want to learn how to edit a document, add notes, and create annotations, make sure to watch this next video.",
